John Doe's content
Africa entered the twenty-first century with large gaps in infrastructure, human capital, and institutions compared with other parts of the developing world. If Africa is to compete, it must get these basics right, but efforts to strengthen the investment climate on their own have not succeeded in helping Africa to reverse its industrial decline. We believe some unconventional wisdom is needed as well.
